<h3><strong><br />Life On Board</strong></h3>
<p>You are invited on an unforgettable journey along the Danube, Rhine, or Rhône &amp; Saône with the <strong>Amadeus</strong> fleet of luxury cruisers. The tastefully furnished ships (<strong>Amadeus</strong> Princess, Brilliant, Diamond, Elegant, Symphony and its flagship <strong>Amadeus</strong> Silver) stand out for their modern elegance, exceptional spaciousness and relaxed atmosphere. They are luxurious floating hotels and you can expect superb service and hospitality from an experienced English speaking tour manager and a friendly crew.<strong><br />Cabins</strong> | 70-80 | All tastefully furnished cabins are outside facing and have seating area and en suite shower, wc. Haydn cabins on the lower deck have windows (do not open), Strauss cabins on the middle deck and Mozart cabins on the upper level have large French balconies (except for <strong>Amadeus</strong> Symphony which has panoramic windows). All cabins are airconditioned and equipped with TV, telephone, safe and hairdryer and are also available for single occupancy. Beds can be separated if required.<br /><br /><strong> Meals</strong> | Full Board Plus </p>
